# 🎨 CSS

---

## 🎯 Theme package

All design tokens live in `@snappy/theme`. Before writing or reviewing SCSS, **read the source files** in
`packages/theme/src/` to learn the available modules, functions, and mixins. Import modules via
`@use "pkg:@snappy/theme/<module>"`.

---

## 📋 Rules

### No hardcoded values

Never write raw colors, font sizes, spacing, radii, shadows, or transitions in component styles. **Always** use the
corresponding SCSS function or mixin from `@snappy/theme`.

### No raw `var(--...)`

Never read CSS custom properties with `var()` in component styles. Use the theme function instead.

### No new CSS custom properties in components

Do not introduce new CSS custom properties (e.g. `--foo`) in component styles. Prefer SCSS variables and theme tokens.
If you need a shared value across components, add a token/mixin to `@snappy/theme` instead.

### Private SCSS variables

If an SCSS variable is used only within a single file, name it as a private variable with a dash prefix: `$-name`.

### Extend the theme, don't bypass it

If the current token set doesn't cover a value you need, add a new token to `@snappy/theme` rather than hardcoding.

### Units

All sizes in **rem**. Exception: borders may use **px** (e.g. `1px solid`).

### Class names

Always **kebab-case** (e.g. `.card-header`, `.nav-item`, `.btn-primary`).

### Avoid `z-index`

Do not use `z-index` unless it is strictly necessary for layering behavior that cannot be achieved by DOM order,
positioning, or natural stacking. If needed, use the smallest possible value and keep layer levels minimal.

---

## ✅ Checklist

- [ ] No hardcoded colors, font sizes, spacing, radii, shadows, or transitions
- [ ] No raw `var(--...)` — theme functions only
- [ ] Sizes in rem; borders in px are ok
- [ ] Class names in kebab-case
- [ ] No `z-index` unless strictly necessary; minimal values only
- [ ] Missing values added to theme, not hardcoded in components
